        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-11-06T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-11-06T18:00:00-05:00" n="265" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d265">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">835.34/9–2846: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Messersmith</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-11-06T18:00:00-05:00">November 6, 1946—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1340. <gloss target="#t_urdes1">Urdes</gloss> 876 Sept 28.<note n="39" xml:id="d265fn39">Not printed.</note> Dept considers release of four
                    demilitarized frigates would seriously prejudice continuation of embargo
                    agreement with British. These vessels are unsuited commercial uses <pb facs="0351" n="333" xml:id="pg_333"/> and easily rearmed. Export license
                    accordingly denied Sept 18 pending further clarification compliance problem.</p>
                <p>Dept concurs your recommendation re Victory ships (<gloss target="#t_urtel1">urtel</gloss> 2372 Nov 4<note n="39a" xml:id="d265fn39a">Not
                        printed.</note>). However, only application so far received by Maritime from
                        Flota<note n="40" xml:id="d265fn40">Flota Mercante del Estado, Argentine
                        Government-controlled shipping organization.</note> is for three regular
                    Victory ships for cargo purposes. Navy unaware objection cited <gloss target="#t_urtel1">urtel</gloss>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
